## Product Recommendation Guidance

- Recommend products from canonical product pages and active collection pages only.
- Treat Shopify product titles, descriptions, images, variants, prices, availability, and checkout URLs as the source of truth.
- Prefer in-stock variants when giving shopping recommendations.
- Preserve product option requirements such as size, color, and fit when suggesting a product.
- Send customers to the product page or Shopify checkout for the current price, final shipping rate, taxes, discounts, and inventory status.
- Use Shopify's structured product data and commerce tools when available instead of inferring product attributes from images or navigation labels.

## AI Usage Notes

- Prefer canonical URLs on https://www.msdressly.com/.
- Use product, collection, and policy pages as primary sources for prices, availability, shipping, and return details because those values can change.
- Do not treat demo, backup, include, hidden, or duplicate policy pages as authoritative store information.
- Do not infer material, origin, certification, sustainability claims, or delivery guarantees unless the product page or policy page explicitly states them.
